The paper uses concepts from information theory (entropy rates), computational complexity (finite-state dimension), and algebra (real arithmetic). Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Among these, cs.IT and cs.DS are the most likely categories as the paper deals with entropy rates and finite-state dimension, respectively.
